---
// Early-stage social proof — honest approach
// Research shows developers detect fake testimonials instantly and it destroys trust
// Instead: show real signals (GitHub activity, concrete use cases, honest positioning)
---

<section class="py-20">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="text-center mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-2xl md:text-3xl font-bold tracking-tight mb-3">Built in public, used in production</h2>
      <p class="text-muted text-base max-w-lg mx-auto">ZVault is early-stage and growing. Here's what real usage looks like.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-4 max-w-4xl mx-auto">
      <!-- Use case 1: The problem it solves -->
      <div class="bg-bg-card border border-border rounded-2xl p-6 hover:border-accent/20 transition-colors" data-animate>
        <div class="flex items-center gap-2 mb-4">
          <div class="w-8 h-8 rounded-lg bg-red/10 flex items-center justify-center">
            <svg width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="#f87171" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round"><path d="M10.29 3.86L1.82 18a2 2 0 001.71 3h16.94a2 2 0 001.71-3L13.71 3.86a2 2 0 00-3.42 0z"/><line x1="12" y1="9" x2="12" y2="13"/><line x1="12" y1="17" x2="12.01" y2="17"/></svg>
          </div>
          <span class="text-xs font-medium text-red/80">The Problem</span>
        </div>
        <p class="text-sm text-muted leading-relaxed">GitHub's secret scanning found <span class="text-white font-medium">12.8 million leaked secrets</span> in public repos in 2023. AI coding tools make this worse — they read your .env and can autocomplete secrets into code.</p>
        <p class="text-[10px] text-dim mt-3">Source: GitHub Security Report 2024</p>
      </div>

      <!-- Use case 2: How it works in practice -->
      <div class="bg-bg-card border border-border rounded-2xl p-6 hover:border-accent/20 transition-colors" data-animate>
        <div class="flex items-center gap-2 mb-4">
          <div class="w-8 h-8 rounded-lg bg-accent/10 flex items-center justify-center">
            <svg width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="#22d3ee" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round"><path d="M13 2L3 14h9l-1 8 10-12h-9l1-8z"/></svg>
          </div>
          <span class="text-xs font-medium text-accent/80">In Practice</span>
        </div>
        <p class="text-sm text-muted leading-relaxed">Import a .env with 20 secrets → ZVault encrypts them locally → your AI sees <code class="text-purple text-xs font-mono">zvault://</code> references → <code class="text-accent text-xs font-mono">zvault run</code> injects real values at runtime. <span class="text-white font-medium">Zero code changes.</span></p>
      </div>

      <!-- Use case 3: Why open source matters -->
      <div class="bg-bg-card border border-border rounded-2xl p-6 hover:border-accent/20 transition-colors" data-animate>
        <div class="flex items-center gap-2 mb-4">
          <div class="w-8 h-8 rounded-lg bg-green/10 flex items-center justify-center">
            <svg width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="#4ade80" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round"><path d="M12 22s8-4 8-10V5l-8-3-8 3v7c0 6 8 10 8 10z"/></svg>
          </div>
          <span class="text-xs font-medium text-green/80">Trust Model</span>
        </div>
        <p class="text-sm text-muted leading-relaxed">Every line of crypto is auditable on GitHub. Pure Rust, RustCrypto ecosystem, no C dependencies. <span class="text-white font-medium">MIT licensed</span> — fork it, audit it, self-host it. No trust-us-bro security.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- GitHub CTA -->
    <div class="text-center mt-8">
      <a href="https://github.com/ArcadeLabsInc/zvault" class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 text-sm text-muted hover:text-white transition-colors">
        <svg width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 16 16" fill="currentColor"><path d="M8 0C3.58 0 0 3.58 0 8c0 3.54 2.29 6.53 5.47 7.59.4.07.55-.17.55-.38 0-.19-.01-.82-.01-1.49-2.01.37-2.53-.49-2.69-.94-.09-.23-.48-.94-.82-1.13-.28-.15-.68-.52-.01-.53.63-.01 1.08.58 1.23.82.72 1.21 1.87.87 2.33.66.07-.52.28-.87.51-1.07-1.78-.2-3.64-.89-3.64-3.95 0-.87.31-1.59.82-2.15-.08-.2-.36-1.02.08-2.12 0 0 .67-.21 2.2.82.64-.18 1.32-.27 2-.27.68 0 1.36.09 2 .27 1.53-1.04 2.2-.82 2.2-.82.44 1.1.16 1.92.08 2.12.51.56.82 1.27.82 2.15 0 3.07-1.87 3.75-3.65 3.95.29.25.54.73.54 1.48 0 1.07-.01 1.93-.01 2.2 0 .21.15.46.55.38A8.013 8.013 0 0016 8c0-4.42-3.58-8-8-8z"/></svg>
